<subSubSection box="[151,585,1826,1853]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,585,1826,1853]" box="[151,585,1826,1853]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,585,1826,1853]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,585,1826,1853]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[151,410,1826,1853]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,410,1826,1853]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cypselurus oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1899,2033]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,150,1041]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The history of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1838" box="[369,495,1899,1925]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[369,495,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[517,627,1899,1925]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[517,627,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group began with the work of 
<bibRefCitation author="Valenciennes, A." box="[1094,1328,1899,1925]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref88628" refString="Valenciennes, A. (1847) Chapitre X. Des Exocets (Exocoetus, Linn.). In: Cuvier, G. &amp; Valenciennes, A., Histoire naturelle des poissons. Vol. 19. Bertrand, Strasbourg, pp. 64 - 144." type="book" year="1847">Valenciennes (1847)</bibRefCitation>
, who described a new species of flying fish from waters of 
<collectingCountry box="[723,790,1935,1961]" name="China" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">China</collectingCountry>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1847" box="[826,1001,1935,1960]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apus">
<emphasis box="[826,1001,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Exocoetus apus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequently, this name was not used in the literature for almost a century, until 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruun, A. F." box="[629,781,1971,1997]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="180 - 187" refId="ref78000" refString="Bruun, A. F. (1937) Notes sur les types des Exocets decrits par Cuvier et Valenciennes. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Serie 2, 9 (3), 180 - 187." type="journal article" year="1937">Bruun (1937)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the 
<typeStatus box="[967,1015,1971,1997]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1847" box="[1054,1229,1971,1996]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apus">
<emphasis box="[1054,1229,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Exocoetus apus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Bruun only mentioned that this species is a member of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Swainson. In 1997" authorityName="Swainson. In" authorityYear="1997" box="[692,1035,2007,2033]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[692,818,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cypselurus</emphasis>
Swainson. In 1997
</taxonomicName>
, Collette 
<emphasis box="[1140,1196,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
re-examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,2007,2033]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
and determine that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1847" box="[370,456,151,176]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apus">
<emphasis box="[370,456,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. apus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker, 1865" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[731,1042,150,177]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[731,873,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. oligolepis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bleeker, P." box="[882,1042,150,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="105 - 129" refId="ref77741" refString="Bleeker, P. (1865) Sur les especes d'exocet de l'Inde Archipelagique. Nederlandsch Tijdschrift voor de Dierkunde, 3, 105 - 129." type="journal article" year="1865">Bleeker, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but the former name has not been used as valid since the original description while the latter was widely used. Therefore, following the Code (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref81606" refString="ICZN (1999) International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition. Published by The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 106 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1847" box="[231,315,223,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="apus">
<emphasis box="[231,315,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. apus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be regarded as nomen oblitum and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[797,938,223,249]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[797,938,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as nomen protectum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
In 1865, Bleeker described three similar species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[761,994,259,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[761,994,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Exocoetus oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[1010,1179,259,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis box="[1010,1179,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1236,1374,259,285]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[1236,1374,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[171,1416,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@14.[171,1416,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. Flying fish drawings from Bleeker 1866-1872: (A)—Exocoetus oligolepis; (B)—E. brachysoma; (C)—E. neglectus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6378627" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6378627/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bleeker, P." box="[345,508,294,321]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="105 - 129" refId="ref77741" refString="Bleeker, P. (1865) Sur les especes d'exocet de l'Inde Archipelagique. Nederlandsch Tijdschrift voor de Dierkunde, 3, 105 - 129." type="journal article" year="1865">Bleeker (1865</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bleeker, P." box="[521,578,295,322]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="67 - 78" refId="ref77768" refString="Bleeker, P. (1866 - 1872). Exocoetiformes. In: Bleeker, P., Atlas ichthyologique des Indes Orientales Neerlandaises. Tom. 6. Frederic Muller, Amsterdam, pp. 67 - 78, pls. Scombres I - V." type="book chapter" year="1866">1866</bibRefCitation>
–1872), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[672,815,295,321]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[672,815,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other two species in fewer scales in a row along side of body, a stockier body and a blunt and convex snout. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[928,1186,331,357]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis box="[928,1186,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Exocoetus brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other two species in a more pointed snout, and also from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[680,817,367,393]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[680,817,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a deeper body, larger head and fewer dorsal-fin rays (10–11 vs. 12–13). Subsequently, however, the validity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[798,966,403,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis box="[798,966,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1018,1154,403,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[1018,1154,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was questioned. As early 
<bibRefCitation author="Gunther, A." box="[151,242,439,465]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref80591" refString="Gunther, A. (1866) Catalogue of the Fishes in the British Museum. Vol. 6. British Museum (Natural History), London, 368 pp." type="book" year="1866">as 1866</bibRefCitation>
, Günther suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[526,696,439,465]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis box="[526,696,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[753,892,439,465]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[753,892,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be synonymous (noting, however, that the latter species has a slightly more elongate body). Günther considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[941,1110,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis box="[941,1110,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species and stated that it differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[360,500,511,537]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[360,500,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in shorter pelvic fins that reach only to the middle of the anal-fin base (vs. to the end of the anal-fin base in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[407,549,547,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[407,549,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, later 
<bibRefCitation author="Weber, M. &amp; de Beaufort, L. F." box="[747,1072,547,573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref88803" refString="Weber, M. &amp; de Beaufort, L. F. (1922) The fishes of the Indo-Australian Archipelago. Vol. 4. E. J. Brill Ltd., Leiden, 410 pp." type="book" year="1922">Weber &amp; de Beaufort (1922)</bibRefCitation>
placed both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[1219,1388,547,573]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis box="[1219,1388,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[151,290,583,609]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[151,290,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[511,654,583,609]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[511,654,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and placed this species into the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson. In" authorityYear="1997" box="[1106,1232,583,609]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1232,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bleeker" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[342,479,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[342,479,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[835,978,619,645]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[835,978,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Herre, A. W." box="[1020,1165,618,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref81001" refString="Herre, A. W. (1953) Check list of Philippine fishes. Research Report 20. Fish and Wildlife Service. United States Government Printing Office, Washington, D. C., 977 pp." type="book" year="1953">Herre (1953)</bibRefCitation>
and Parin (
<bibRefCitation author="Parin, N. V." box="[1292,1432,619,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="205 - 285" refId="ref85110" refString="Parin, N. V. (1960 a) Flying fishes (Exocoetidae) of North-West Pacific. Trudy Instituta Okeanologii, 31, 205 - 285. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1960">Parin 1960a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Parin, N. V. &amp; Besednov, L. N." box="[151,425,654,681]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="104 - 117" refId="ref85787" refString="Parin, N. V. &amp; Besednov, L. N. (1965) Flying fishes (Oxyporhamphidae and Exocoetidae) of the Gulf of Tonkin. Trudy Instituta Okeanologii, 80, 104 - 117. [in Russian with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1965">Parin &amp; Besednov 1965</bibRefCitation>
), though the latter author noted that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[838,982,655,681]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[838,982,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is likely a composite species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fowler, H. W. &amp; Steinitz, H." pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="3 - 4" refId="ref79674" refString="Fowler, H. W. &amp; Steinitz, H. (1956) Fishes from Cyprus, Iran, Iraq, Israel and Oman. Bulletin of the Research Council of Israel. Section B. Biology and Geology, 5 B (3 - 4), 260 - 292." type="journal article" year="1956">Fowler &amp; Steinitz (1956)</bibRefCitation>
also regarded that 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker" authorityName="Bleeker" box="[530,761,691,717]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[530,667,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
Bleeker
</taxonomicName>
(as well as 
<taxonomicName authority="Steindachner" authorityName="Steindachner" box="[892,1201,691,718]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="socotranus">
<emphasis box="[892,1046,691,716]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. socotranus</emphasis>
Steindachner
</taxonomicName>
) is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker. Since" authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[183,589,727,753]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[183,417,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Exocoetus oligolepis</emphasis>
Bleeker. Since
</taxonomicName>
then, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1865" box="[662,832,727,753]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis box="[662,832,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[890,1029,727,753]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[890,1029,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
firmly remained in the lists of synonyms for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[275,419,763,789]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[275,419,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where they are at present (
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke, R. &amp; Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; Van der Laan, R." box="[735,942,763,789]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref79818" refString="Fricke, R., Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; Van der Laan, R. (Eds.) (2021) Eschmeyer's Catalog of Fishes: genera, species, references. Electronic Version. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp (accessed 15 April 2021)" type="url" year="2021">
Fricke 
<emphasis box="[816,874,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Parin, N. V." box="[1079,1221,763,790]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="43 - 58" refId="ref85366" refString="Parin, N. V. (1967) Chapter 2. Beloniform fishes of the open ocean. In: Kort, V. G. &amp; Rass, T. S. (Eds.), Pacific Ocean. Biology of the Pacific Ocean. Book 3. Fishes of open waters. Nauka, Moscow, pp. 43 - 58. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1967">Parin (1967)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovalevskaya, N. V." pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="212 - 275" refId="ref82681" refString="Kovalevskaya, N. V. (1980) The reproduction, development and peculiarities of distribution of the larvae and fry of flyingfishes in the Pacific and Indian Oceans. Trudy Instituta Okeanologii, 97, 212 - 275. [in Russian with English abstract]" type="journal article" year="1980">Kovalevskaya (1980)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName box="[300,439,799,825]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[300,439,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among valid species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson. In" authorityYear="1997" box="[824,950,799,825]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[824,950,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without explanation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Our examination of specimens previously identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[820,962,835,861]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[820,962,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed that six species (two of them also include subspecies) had been lumped under this name. These species and subspecies are very difficult to distinguish as adults but much easier to distinguish as juveniles. Four of these, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[899,1041,907,933]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[899,1041,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin, 2022" authorityName="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin" authorityYear="2022" box="[1055,1155,907,933]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="izumii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1055,1155,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. izumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1162,1251,907,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1162,1251,907,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin, 2022" authorityName="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin" authorityYear="2022" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="clariangulatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. clariangulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[191,281,943,969]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[191,281,943,969]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[336,476,943,969]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[336,476,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we place in the 
<emphasis box="[667,693,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C.</emphasis>
“ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bleeker. Since" authorityYear="1865" box="[713,823,943,969]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Exocoetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oligolepis">
<emphasis box="[713,823,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">oligolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group. The other species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin, 2022" authorityName="Shakhovskoy &amp; Parin" authorityYear="2022" box="[1222,1339,943,969]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nossibe" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1222,1339,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. nossibe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1346,1436,943,969]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1346,1436,943,969]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[199,366,979,1005]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[199,325,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cypselurus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, are more distant relatives; we place the former in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson. In" authorityYear="1997" box="[1090,1216,979,1005]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1090,1216,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cypselurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1223,1283,979,1005]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and the latter is probably synonymous with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[489,673,1015,1041]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Exocoetidae" genus="Cypselurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Beloniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="poecilopterus">
<emphasis box="[489,673,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. poecilopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
